WEBVTT

00:18.235 --> 00:27.592
♪♪

00:30.639 --> 00:35.209
Montgomery:
The world is not made of atoms.

00:35.209 --> 00:39.039
It is made of stories.

00:39.039 --> 01:05.065
♪♪

01:05.065 --> 01:07.502
[Birds cawing]

01:07.502 --> 01:25.085
♪♪

01:25.085 --> 01:27.087
[Panting]

01:27.087 --> 01:55.550
♪♪

01:55.550 --> 01:57.595
[Streetcar bell dings ]

01:57.595 --> 02:06.691
♪♪

02:06.691 --> 02:08.650
[Blade sharpening]

02:08.650 --> 02:14.830
♪♪

02:14.830 --> 02:18.007
[Tires screech,
bike bell jingles]

02:18.007 --> 02:23.795
♪♪

02:23.795 --> 02:25.797
[Bell tolling]

02:25.797 --> 02:40.769
♪♪

02:40.769 --> 02:42.988
[Bird squawking in distance]

02:42.988 --> 03:36.216
♪♪

03:36.216 --> 03:38.696
[Click, doorbell tolls]

03:41.003 --> 04:14.384
♪♪

04:14.384 --> 04:15.907
Aah!

04:15.907 --> 04:24.046
♪♪

04:24.046 --> 04:26.962
Hello, child.

04:26.962 --> 04:30.052
♪♪

04:30.052 --> 04:32.620
You've left
your camera!

04:32.620 --> 04:44.153
♪♪

04:44.153 --> 04:46.764
Suck it, creep-o!

04:46.764 --> 04:55.207
♪♪

05:02.258 --> 05:04.956
Creep-o.

05:04.956 --> 05:06.871
That's a new one.

05:06.871 --> 05:08.917
[Clock chiming]

05:13.878 --> 05:20.494
[Chuckles]

05:20.494 --> 05:24.715
What is life but a story?

05:24.715 --> 05:28.719
A single narrative thread
in the tapestry

05:28.719 --> 05:32.636
that binds us all.

05:32.636 --> 05:34.638
And as with all stories,

05:34.638 --> 05:39.077
it is not the length
of the tale that resonates,

05:39.077 --> 05:43.865
it is the quality
of the content within.

05:43.865 --> 05:47.782
I beseech you, friends,
that even as we mourn,

05:47.782 --> 05:54.615
let us celebrate as a tribute
to this young man's story.

05:54.615 --> 05:58.227
Let us seek solace that
we have been granted impunity

05:58.227 --> 06:00.229
from eternal rest.

06:00.229 --> 06:02.797
That death would not
eradicate us,

06:02.797 --> 06:07.149
but in the pages of life
we will continue forth

06:07.149 --> 06:11.022
and we cannot die!

06:11.022 --> 06:14.504
♪♪

06:20.162 --> 06:26.211
Uh, and now a reading
from Corinthians.

06:26.211 --> 06:28.649
Thank you for coming.

06:28.649 --> 06:32.435
Please drive safely.

06:32.435 --> 06:35.003
Sorry for your loss.

06:35.003 --> 06:37.179
Thank you for coming.

06:37.179 --> 06:40.574
♪♪

06:40.574 --> 06:42.837
[Wind howling]

06:42.837 --> 06:45.405
♪♪

06:45.405 --> 06:49.104
[Thunder rumbles]

06:49.104 --> 06:51.236
[Birds cawing]

06:51.236 --> 07:58.216
♪♪

07:58.216 --> 08:02.220
[Coffin creaking]I wouldn't.

08:02.220 --> 08:04.745
This world,
this business,

08:04.745 --> 08:09.401
it's not as neat and tidy
as one might expect.

08:14.189 --> 08:17.497
The coffin --
It's so small.

08:17.497 --> 08:20.108
A tragic thing,
indeed.

08:20.108 --> 08:24.286
Montgomery Dark,
resident mortician,

08:24.286 --> 08:26.723
indentured servant
to the great beyond.

08:26.723 --> 08:28.856
Dark. Really?

08:28.856 --> 08:30.118
Mm.

08:30.118 --> 08:34.208
It's a family name.

08:34.208 --> 08:37.429
Oh, I'm Sam.

08:37.429 --> 08:39.344
Sam.

08:39.344 --> 08:41.129
My condolences.

08:41.129 --> 08:43.304
Were you close
with the child?

08:43.304 --> 08:48.005
Oh, no. I'm sorry.
I saw a sign out front.

08:48.005 --> 08:50.268
Sign?

08:50.268 --> 08:53.620
Yeah, "Help wanted."

08:53.620 --> 08:57.101
Are you still looking?

08:57.101 --> 08:59.190
Yes.

08:59.190 --> 09:04.674
Always.

09:04.674 --> 09:06.850
Please.

09:06.850 --> 09:15.642
♪♪

09:15.642 --> 09:19.820
Have you any experience
in the mortuary arts?

09:19.820 --> 09:22.823
No, but I'm
a fast learner.

09:22.823 --> 09:26.870
Mm, most people would
find it unmanageable.

09:26.870 --> 09:29.481
Huh.
I'm not most people.

09:29.481 --> 09:31.353
We shall see.

09:31.353 --> 09:34.835
Please have a seat.

09:34.835 --> 09:38.055
This is -- This is
one serious collection of books

09:38.055 --> 09:39.361
you've got here.

09:39.361 --> 09:40.884
The mere tip
of the looming,

09:40.884 --> 09:44.061
lumbering iceberg,
I'm afraid --

09:44.061 --> 09:46.803
an archive of the various ways
in which clients

09:46.803 --> 09:51.373
have found themselves passing
through our hallowed halls.

09:51.373 --> 09:55.159
So, these are all stories
about how people died?

09:55.159 --> 10:00.469
Not just how,
my dear, why.

10:00.469 --> 10:03.341
Huh. That's
pretty cool.

10:03.341 --> 10:06.257
Yes, it is, isn't it?

10:06.257 --> 10:08.129
[Chuckles]

10:08.129 --> 10:16.180
♪♪

10:16.180 --> 10:17.834
[Sighs]

10:17.834 --> 10:19.880
Tell me one.

10:19.880 --> 10:24.493
Tell you one what?A story.

10:24.493 --> 10:27.931
Something...
dark and twisted.

10:27.931 --> 10:30.586
Something awesome.

10:30.586 --> 10:34.242
Mm. Perhaps we should
stick to business.

10:34.242 --> 10:35.852
We have much to do.

10:35.852 --> 10:37.375
Oh, come on, Monty.
If I'm going to be working here,

10:37.375 --> 10:39.073
I need to know what
I'm getting myself into.

10:39.073 --> 10:42.642
You are not hired yet,
young lady.

10:44.948 --> 10:47.124
Right because you have
a stack of applications

10:47.124 --> 10:48.648
to go through.

10:48.648 --> 10:58.179
♪♪

10:58.179 --> 11:04.402
Something dark,
twisted, and "awesome," eh?

11:04.402 --> 11:06.840
♪♪

11:06.840 --> 11:10.321
Well, see how
this one grabs you.

11:10.321 --> 11:14.195
♪♪

11:14.195 --> 11:16.110
['50's-era dance music playing]

11:16.110 --> 11:18.112
[Door creaking]

11:18.112 --> 11:30.037
♪♪

11:30.037 --> 11:33.040
[Knock at door]Uh, someone's in here.

11:33.040 --> 11:35.607
Man: Hoping you're
not trying to hide from me.

11:35.607 --> 11:37.479
I wouldn't dream of it.

11:37.479 --> 11:38.828
[Chuckles] Okay.

11:38.828 --> 11:42.789
Meet me
on the veranda in 10?

11:42.789 --> 11:45.443
Look, I've just got to say that
talking with you back there,

11:45.443 --> 11:48.577
I felt this connection, and
I feel like you felt it, too.

11:48.577 --> 11:50.231
A-Am I being crazy?

11:50.231 --> 11:54.670
I'm being crazy.
I'll see you on the veranda.

11:54.670 --> 11:57.325
[Sighs]

11:57.325 --> 12:16.561
♪♪

12:16.561 --> 12:18.955
[Metal screeching]

12:28.399 --> 12:33.230
♪♪

12:33.230 --> 12:35.189
Ahh.

12:41.456 --> 13:08.352
♪♪

13:08.352 --> 13:10.528
[Toilet flushes]

13:10.528 --> 13:18.362
♪♪

13:18.362 --> 13:20.843
[Inhales deeply]
Okay.

13:20.843 --> 13:22.932
♪♪

13:22.932 --> 13:25.239
[Thump]

13:25.239 --> 13:52.657
♪♪

13:52.657 --> 13:54.007
Okay.

13:54.007 --> 13:56.357
Ahh!
[Inhales sharply]

13:56.357 --> 13:58.838
Damn it.

14:09.805 --> 14:19.249
♪♪

14:19.249 --> 14:21.382
[Grunting softly]

14:21.382 --> 14:25.734
♪♪

14:25.734 --> 14:28.345
[Grunting]

14:28.345 --> 14:32.349
♪♪

14:32.349 --> 14:34.482
Aaaah!

14:34.482 --> 14:36.484
[Creature trilling]

14:36.484 --> 14:53.718
♪♪

14:53.718 --> 14:56.983
[People murmuring casually]

14:56.983 --> 15:01.204
[Softly]
Can somebody help me?

15:01.204 --> 15:03.380
Help me, please!

15:03.380 --> 15:05.382
[Murmuring continues]

15:17.481 --> 15:20.006
[Distant creature trill]

15:22.573 --> 15:24.619
[Floor creaking]

15:26.795 --> 15:29.102
[Distant creature trill]

15:29.102 --> 15:40.940
♪♪

15:40.940 --> 15:42.202
[Shatter]

15:42.202 --> 15:44.378
[Ticking]

15:44.378 --> 15:46.641
[Ticking slows]

15:52.734 --> 15:55.171
[Ticking stops][Creature growling]

15:57.565 --> 15:59.567
[Creature roars]

15:59.567 --> 16:07.053
♪♪

16:07.053 --> 16:10.970
Aaaaah!

16:10.970 --> 16:21.371
♪♪

16:21.371 --> 16:24.026
[Gasps]

16:24.026 --> 16:27.551
[Bones crunching]

16:27.551 --> 16:30.728
[Creature growling in distance]

16:30.728 --> 16:33.253
['50's-era dance music playing]

16:33.253 --> 16:41.391
♪♪

16:41.391 --> 16:43.437
It's not bad.

16:45.787 --> 16:49.182
I was expecting something
a bit more substantial.

16:49.182 --> 16:52.924
Maybe an ironic comeuppance
or a big twist, but...

16:52.924 --> 16:54.883
it was fun.

16:56.580 --> 16:59.366
Fun?

16:59.366 --> 17:01.237
Well, I have
more stories.

17:01.237 --> 17:03.674
Many, many more.

17:03.674 --> 17:07.416
I was...
just warming up.

17:07.416 --> 17:09.897
Here.

17:09.897 --> 17:13.162
Sign here,
initial here and here.

17:15.382 --> 17:18.602
It's a bit far-fetched,
don't you think,

17:18.602 --> 17:20.517
an octopus
in a medicine cabinet?

17:20.517 --> 17:22.737
It was not an octopus.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.391
And [breathes deeply]

17:24.391 --> 17:26.262
it is not the validity
of the story

17:26.262 --> 17:29.483
that concerns me,
but the message within.

17:29.483 --> 17:31.789
And the message is...

17:31.789 --> 17:34.792
don't stick you nose
where it doesn't belong?

17:34.792 --> 17:38.883
In a most
basic sense, yes.

17:38.883 --> 17:42.104
But on a deeper level,

17:42.104 --> 17:47.370
it is about the universal
balance of all things.

17:47.370 --> 17:49.372
♪♪

17:49.372 --> 17:52.114
Universal balance?

17:52.114 --> 17:57.119
♪♪

17:57.119 --> 18:00.862
There we are --
nice and neat.

18:00.862 --> 18:02.820
Shall we begin?

18:02.820 --> 18:07.521
♪♪

18:07.521 --> 18:10.959
[Thunder crashes]

18:10.959 --> 18:15.703
The foyer, French for
where the fire is kept.

18:15.703 --> 18:18.575
Oh, who are
these ghouls?

18:18.575 --> 18:21.535
Ghouls?

18:21.535 --> 18:23.928
These are morticians,
my dear,

18:23.928 --> 18:27.497
some of whom were called
to serve in this very house.

18:27.497 --> 18:31.153
A distinguished group,
to be sure.

18:31.153 --> 18:35.157
[Chuckles]
Yeah, distinguished.

18:35.157 --> 18:38.726
Come.
There's much to see.

18:38.726 --> 18:44.384
♪♪

18:44.384 --> 18:48.518
Of course, you've already seen
the viewing parlor.

18:48.518 --> 18:51.173
Very elementary.

18:51.173 --> 18:53.523
The mourning sit here

18:53.523 --> 18:58.528
and up here
resides the rhapsodist.

18:58.528 --> 19:00.922
How old are you?

19:00.922 --> 19:04.578
Ironic, is it not,
that one so old would preside

19:04.578 --> 19:08.669
over the passing
of one so young.

19:08.669 --> 19:11.672
So, what is
the story here?

19:11.672 --> 19:13.282
[Coffin creaks]

19:13.282 --> 19:16.111
[Slams shut]

19:16.111 --> 19:18.635
I would rather not.

19:18.635 --> 19:22.944
Some tales even I find
too unsettling to recount.

19:24.250 --> 19:27.340
Tell me
another one, then.

19:27.340 --> 19:30.256
You say you have
better stories.

19:30.256 --> 19:31.953
I want to hear them.

19:31.953 --> 19:39.178
♪♪

19:39.178 --> 19:42.833
You've heard the phrase,
"better safe than sorry,"

19:42.833 --> 19:44.792
I presume?

19:44.792 --> 19:48.796
Well, this young man
had to learn it the hard way.

19:48.796 --> 19:51.842
♪♪

19:51.842 --> 19:54.932
Karl Marx said that
social progress can be measured

19:54.932 --> 19:58.022
by the social position
of the female sex.

19:58.022 --> 20:01.069
Now, ladies,
as a straight, white male,

20:01.069 --> 20:04.377
I'm going to be the first
to admit the tides are turning.

20:04.377 --> 20:06.857
The patriarchy is falling,
and in its place

20:06.857 --> 20:10.339
is a brave, new world
of equality and sexual freedom.

20:10.339 --> 20:13.734
A world where both men and women
are entitled to have sex

20:13.734 --> 20:16.258
whenever and with
whoever they please

20:16.258 --> 20:24.440
as long as they do so safely
and with the proper protection.

20:24.440 --> 20:28.314
Just...like...that.

20:28.314 --> 20:30.620
[Women giggling]

20:30.620 --> 20:33.319
You're empowered.

20:33.319 --> 20:36.235
Please,
have some condoms.

20:36.235 --> 20:38.715
Guys, listen --
We are having a party tonight

20:38.715 --> 20:43.111
at the Sig Delt house.
You should stop by.

20:43.111 --> 20:46.723
Okay?

20:46.723 --> 20:50.466
So...is that true
about the patriarchy?

20:50.466 --> 20:54.818
No, idiot.
Patriarchy is solid.

20:54.818 --> 20:56.211
Karl Marx said that --

20:56.211 --> 20:58.344
You don't even know
who Karl Marx is.

20:58.344 --> 21:00.128
Yeah.
Yeah, I do.

21:00.128 --> 21:02.043
Yes, I do.

21:02.043 --> 21:04.611
Jakey, can you please tell me
what we're doing here?

21:04.611 --> 21:08.484
We are providing an important
service to the incoming freshmen

21:08.484 --> 21:12.880
who are young, impressionable,
and vulnerable.

21:12.880 --> 21:17.188
Guys, it is our job to help them
make informed decisions.

21:17.188 --> 21:19.582
♪♪

21:19.582 --> 21:22.237
And that decision
is to have sex

21:22.237 --> 21:24.457
with you hopeless jerks
at the party tonight.

21:24.457 --> 21:28.983
